  "body": "This change that defaults to supporting eth/66 and eth/67 for all chains (and running two sentries) is incorrect as afaik Polygon and BSC (for example) do not support eth/67, additionally, just incrementing from the --port value is also problematic as it may conflict with other services.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/blob/ecf34b2493209ab1df31750426ccb6240d5b2533/eth/backend.go#L323\r\n\r\nSuggest two fixes:\r\n* have chain specific values for default p2p protocol support\r\n* make it possible to set the port values per p2p protocol and not auto increment them by default",
